\begin_layout Standard
It is important to realize that treatment and control groups need to be
 balanced over all other factors.
 This means that often, we can not use all observations.
 For example, if we want to simply test if being shown any video was effective
 in increasing maize yields, we can not simply compare the 257 control household
s that were shown a video to all households that were shown a video (3,331
 households).
 We need to make sure that within the treatment group, there are equal numbers
 in each cell.
 As such, we need to take the treatment combination with the least observations,
 which are according to the power calculations the combinations where the
 video is shown to the couple and the messenger is either a man or a women
 (BM and BF).
