 Therefore, to test the effectiveness of videos, we compare 257 control
 households to 3,078 households, which corresponds to 342 households in
 each of 9 treatment combination cells.
 Therefore, in each cell that has excess observations, we will take a random
 sample.
 For example, according to the power calculations, we will have 385 households
 in the treatment combination where the messenger is male and the recipient
 is male (MM).
